| Keyword  | Usage                             | Example                 |
| -------- | --------------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| False    | Boolean false value               | `x = False`             |
| True     | Boolean true value                | `x = True`              |
| None     | Represents null / no value        | `x = None`              |
| and      | Logical AND operator              | `5 > 2 and 3 > 1`       |
| or       | Logical OR operator               | `5 > 2 or 1 > 3`        |
| not      | Negates boolean value             | `not True`              |
| if       | Conditional statement             | `if x > 5:`             |
| elif     | Multiple condition checking       | `elif x == 5:`          |
| else     | Executes when condition fails     | `else:`                 |
| for      | Loop through sequence             | `for i in range(5):`    |
| while    | Loop while condition true         | `while x < 5:`          |
| break    | Stops loop immediately            | `break`                 |
| continue | Skips current iteration           | `continue`              |
| pass     | Placeholder / empty statement     | `pass`                  |
| in       | Membership operator               | `3 in [1,2,3]`          |
| is       | Checks object identity            | `a is b`                |
| def      | Defines a function                | `def add():`            |
| return   | Returns value from function       | `return x`              |
| lambda   | Anonymous function                | `lambda x: x+1`         |
| class    | Defines a class                   | `class Person:`         |
| try      | Starts exception handling         | `try:`                  |
| except   | Handles exceptions                | `except Exception:`     |
| finally  | Executes always after try         | `finally:`              |
| raise    | Raises exception manually         | `raise ValueError()`    |
| assert   | Debugging check                   | `assert x > 0`          |
| import   | Imports module                    | `import math`           |
| from     | Imports specific part             | `from math import sqrt` |
| as       | Creates alias                     | `import numpy as np`    |
| global   | Declares global variable          | `global x`              |
| nonlocal | Refers to outer function variable | `nonlocal x`            |
| with     | Used with context manager         | `with open('file'):`    |
| async    | Defines async function            | `async def main():`     |
| await    | Waits for async result            | `await task`            |
| del      | Deletes object                    | `del x`                 |
| yield    | Returns generator value           | `yield 1`               |
